    "body": "## Summary\nFix critical severity security issue in `src/mpack/mpack_core.c`.\n\n## Vulnerability\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **ID** | V-003 |\n| **Severity** | CRITICAL |\n| **Scanner** | multi_agent_ai |\n| **Rule** | `V-003` |\n| **File** | `src/mpack/mpack_core.c:125` |\n| **CWE** | CWE-120 |\n\n**Description**: The MessagePack parser in mpack_core.c performs four memcpy operations using lengths (count, write_cnt) derived directly from incoming serialized data fields. These lengths are not validated against the actual destination buffer capacity before the copy is performed. An attacker who controls the MessagePack stream — achievable by acting as or compromising an LSP server — can craft messages with length fields that exceed the destination buffer size, causing heap buffer overflows that corrupt heap metadata and enable arbitrary code execution.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/mpack/mpack_core.c`\n\n## Verification\n- [x] Build passes\n- [x] Scanner re-scan confirms fix\n- [x] LLM code review passed\n\n---\n*Automated security fix by [OrbisAI Security](https://orbisappsec.com)*\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-04T09:42:31Z",
